{
  "page": "Skahazadhan",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Slavers_Bay.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Skahazadhan is located in Slaver&#39;s Bay\"><img alt=\"Skahazadhan is located in Slaver&#39;s Bay\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/09/Slavers_Bay.png/300px-Slavers_Bay.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"297\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/09/Slavers_Bay.png/450px-Slavers_Bay.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/09/Slavers_Bay.png/600px-Slavers_Bay.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 15.6%; left: 90.3%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -4px; top: -4px; width: 8px; font-size: 8px; z-index:100;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/8px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Skahazadhan\" width=\"8\" height=\"8\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/12px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/16px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size:&#160;%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; left: -6.5em; text-align: right;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\">Skahazadhan</span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\"><a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a> and the location of the Skahazadhan\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The <b>Skahazadhan</b> is a major river of <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>. It begins in the southeastern <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a> and flows southwest through <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> into <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>. South of the river are <a href=\"/index.php/Lhazar\" title=\"Lhazar\">Lhazar</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_waste\" title=\"Red waste\">red waste</a>. Cities on its tributaries include <a href=\"/index.php/Vaes_Mejhah\" title=\"Vaes Mejhah\">Vaes Mejhah</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Krazaaj_Has\" title=\"Krazaaj Has\">Krazaaj Has</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Kosrak\" title=\"Kosrak\">Kosrak</a>. A tributary also flows through the <a href=\"/index.php/Khyzai_Pass\" title=\"Khyzai Pass\">Khyzai Pass</a> near Meereen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiaf_the_dothraki_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiaf_the_dothraki_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Skahazadhan is a slow river with brown water. The Meereenese use it for waste and instead drink from deep wells.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Pike\" title=\"Pike\">Pike</a> are found in the river.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_River\" title=\"Warden of the River\">Warden of the River</a> is a title granted to officials monitoring the Skahazadhan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg/350px-Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg/525px-Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg 1.5x, /images/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> by Martina Pilcerova © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>After the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Scarb\" title=\"Scarb\">Scarb</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ben_Plumm\" title=\"Ben Plumm\">Ben Plumm</a> fled <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> by escaping through the sewers which empty into the Skahazadhan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>To resolve the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Siege of Meereen\">siege of Meereen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> sends a group into the <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">the city</a> by infiltrating the sewers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Second siege of Meereen\">second siege of Meereen</a>, galleys from <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/New_Ghis\" title=\"New Ghis\">New Ghis</a> and a carrack from <a href=\"/index.php/Tolos\" title=\"Tolos\">Tolos</a> seal off the Skahazadhan,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and two <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_legions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iron legions\">iron legions</a> are to land north of the river to block Meereenese access to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Masters\" title=\"Wise Masters\">Wise Masters</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> set up <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slave</a> pens and an auction block on the southern shore of the river, where it meets <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Daenerys, now <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_Meereen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of Meereen\">Queen of Meereen</a>, disappears from <a href=\"/index.php/Daznak%27s_Pit\" title=\"Daznak&#39;s Pit\">Daznak's Pit</a>, her <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodrider\" title=\"Bloodrider\">bloodriders</a> are sent in search of her north of the Skahazadhan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> King <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a> styles himself <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_the_Skahazadhan\" title=\"Master of the Skahazadhan\">Master of the Skahazadhan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a> declines the ancient office of <a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_River\" title=\"Warden of the River\">Warden of the River</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> stood on a jut of sand and stone where the slow brown Skahazadhan flowed into <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>. The city's north wall ran along the riverbank, its west along the bay shore.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Most of the <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkish</a> host drew their drinking water from the Skahazadhan, which Tyrion had known was a very bad idea even before the healer's warning. The clever ones took care to stay upstream of the latrines, but they were still downstream of <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">the city</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Two days ago, climbing on a spire of rock, she had spied water to the south, a slender thread that glittered briefly as the sun was going down. A stream, Dany decided. Small, but it would lead her to a larger stream, and that stream would flow into some little river, and all the rivers in <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">this part of the world</a> were vassals of the Skahazadhan. Once she found the Skahazadhan she need only follow it downstream to <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Skahazadhan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiaf_the_dothraki_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiaf_the_dothraki_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>,  The Dothraki Sea.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_57\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 57\">Chapter 57</a>, Daenerys V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_2\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 2\">Chapter 2</a>, Daenerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rad